              <h3>Electric Dryer Repair</h3>
              <p>
                Electric dryers are popular because of their easy installation and lower upfront cost. However, over time, they can develop a range of issues that need professional attention. Common problems include a malfunctioning heating element, faulty thermostats, and blown thermal fuses, which prevent the dryer from heating up. A broken drive belt can stop the drum from spinning, and a defective timer can disrupt the drying cycle. At Same Day Appliance Repair, we often get called to fix these problems, and our technicians are trained to diagnose electrical issues and replace damaged parts. We also clean the venting system to prevent overheating and fire hazards.
              </p>
            </div>

