              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Dryer Thermostat Repair: Dryer Overheating or Not Heating At All</h3>
              <p>
                Your dryer's thermostats control the internal temperature to ensure your clothes dry appropriately without overheating. Most dryers have multiple thermostats, a high-limit thermostat, and a cycling thermostat that work together to keep the temperature consistent. When a thermostat fails, it can cause your dryer to overheat or not heat at all. Diagnosing a faulty thermostat is a simple process with a multimeter; our technicians are experts at this repair. Many of our customers come to us for thermostat issues and we can replace faulty thermostats quickly to get proper airflow and heat regulation for optimal dryer performance.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Drum Belt Repair: Drum Stopped Spinning</h3>
              <p>
                The drum belt is a critical component that connects the motor to the drum so it can spin and tumble clothes. Over time, this belt can wear out, stretch, or break, and the drum will stop spinning. If your dryer is running but the drum isn’t turning the drum belt is probably the issue. At Same Day Appliance Repair, we replace worn-out drum belts for our customers all the time to get the tumbling action back so your clothes dry evenly. Replacing the drum belt involves disassembling the dryer and installing a new belt; our technicians are experts at this.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
